I also regret not being introduced to this site before today, it probably would have solved alot of headaches.<br>
<br>
First, I have always been angry with the fact that a bard, with less than a third of my experience can fly past my SoW'd or wolf formed self like I was standing still.  Don't get me wrong, I think SoW is a wonderful spell, and a godsend at lower levels, but as mentioned in the petition, with the advent of Luclin, and the immunity of some creatures to changes in movement speed, SoW is simply not reasonable past 40.  My suggestion was a simple upgrade to SoW with the 39'th spell ring.  This could be acomplished either by moving SoC and making it targetable and longer duration, or creating an entirely new spell all together for this purpose.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I feel that druids should have more magic based DD's with stun effects later in life.  I have researched this and it seems that Fury of air is the last magic based dd/stun spell we get.  I would like to see an updrade to this implimented in the 49th or 50'th spell circle, and allowing it to be cast indoors would be nice too, but not absloutely necessary.  <br>
<br>
Lastly, and this is the only thing I disagree with in the petition, though I signed it, is that in the high end game especially, the druid skin line should be able to stack with clerical buffs.  The reason for this was made quite clear in the petition, Creatures are hitting ALOT harder than they used to, and with the rampage ability, they cause alot more damage to ALOT more people at once.  I can not count the times I have seen a giant go into rampage and hit everyone on the raid for enormous amounts of damage, I am fairly sure this was because of the large melee radius which mobs are allowed to use (Even though it is obviously physically beyond their ability to reach that far.)  Enabling the buffs to stack would make a measurable difference in the in the amount of damage taken and thus make the druid much more viable in raid situations, once again making their heals beneficial since it would appear that the damage the caster will take will have slowed down significantly.<br>
<br>
Please also note that I have solo'd very little and actually prefer groups for hunting, and I personally feel that quadding is rude to other players unless you are in an under used area.  I prefer the root/dot method when I solo, so you will understand where my ideas are comming from.<br>
<br>
